# {{projectName}}

> {{description}}

A [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) server built with TypeScript
and the official `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`, speaking over stdio.

## Quick start

```bash
npm install
npm run build
npm run inspect   # explore the server in the MCP Inspector
```

## Register with an MCP client

After building, point your client at the compiled server. For Claude Code, add to `.mcp.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{projectName}}": { "command": "node", "args": ["dist/index.js"] }
  }
}
```

## Add a tool

Tools live in `src/tools.ts` as pure functions plus a zod input schema, registered in
`src/index.ts`:

```ts
server.registerTool(
  'my_tool',
  { title: 'My Tool', description: '…', inputSchema: { q: z.string() } },
  async ({ q }) => ({ content: [{ type: 'text', text: doSomething(q) }] }),
);
```

> **Important:** never `console.log` — stdout is the protocol channel. Log to stderr.

